- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper utilizes text transcriptions to improve the performance of voice conversion, which involves the intersection of speech and language processing. 
- cs.LG (Learning): The paper proposes a multi-task learning structure and a data-augmentation method to improve the performance of voice conversion, which involves machine learning techniques. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes methods to improve the performance of voice conversion, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): Although the paper does not directly involve computer vision, some voice conversion techniques utilize visual information (e.g., lip movements) to improve the conversion performance. Therefore, cs.CV could also be a possible sub-category.
